This paper presents a novel method for panoptic segmentation, which is a task in computer vision that combines instance segmentation and semantic segmentation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also utilizes object detection and instance center prediction, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The method involves processing images in real-time, which could fall under robotics (cs.RO) or multimedia (cs.MM) categories.
